orangelight.title: Use Shibboleth instead of CAS for Authentication

comments.body:
- [ ] Add Shibboleth/SAML Support to the Catalog via gems? - need to research options
- [ ] Work with OIT's IAM (Identity and Access Management) Group to set up catalog-staging and catalog-production as trusted endpoints with our campus shibboleth IDP at https://idp.princeton.edu/idp/shibboleth. 
- [ ] Identify a strategy for local testing of Shibboleth Authentication/Authorization. - need to research options
- [ ] Make sure a successful shib response includes the attribute urn:oid:1.2.840.113556.1.2.613/employeeType" which is not part of the standard set of attributes released via Shib.  The groupings in this value are what we use to determine access to electronic resources. 
- [ ] Update Borrow Direct authorization route to allow only appropriate employee type groups to access Borrow Direct. 
- [ ] Update Request gem to allow pick-up, in library use, and digitization requests only by appropriate employee type groupings.
